It is shown in this PR that the forget functor from commutative groups to groups preserves all limits (regardless of the universe parameters of the index category). It is also shown that a functor `F : J â¥¤ CommGroupCat` (or `F : J â¥¤ GroupCat`) has a limit iff the type `(F â‹™ forget _).sections` is small. This is related to the fact that the forget functor `CommGroupCat.{u} â¥¤ Type u` is corepresentable (by `ULift â„¤`).
